    "result": {"data":{"strapiPost":{"strapiId":5500,"title":"Butterfield Trail Pending Recognition As National Historic Trail ","topic":"Highlight","slug":"butterfield-trail-pending-president-s-signature-for-recognition-as-national-historic-trail","coverImage":{"publicURL":"/static/d5438e57c9983cc1d3537be1d042fc6d/caae7b86266c8fe071577c47be2bbe3a.jpeg"},"photoCredit":"Encyclopedia of Arkansas","date":"2023-01-04","content":"<p>A bill authored by Sen. John Boozman that would designate <a href=\"https://www.5newsonline.com/article/news/regional/arkansas-news/butterfield-trail-arkansas-national-historic-trail/527-3235b37f-2459-4c6d-a183-ac38e000a2eb\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Butterfield Overland Trail</a><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> as a </span><a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2022/12/butterfield-trail-will-be-a-national-historic-trail-with-president-bidens-signature/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">National Historic Trail</a> is awaiting President Biden's signature to make it final. </p><ul><li><strong>Westward</strong>: At approximately 3,553 miles, <a href=\"https://arkansasheritagetrails.com/Butterfield/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Butterfield Trail</a> was the longest stagecoach operation in world history and was used to transport passengers and mail between St. Louis, Memphis, and San Fransisco.</li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Snail mail</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">: The </span><a href=\"https://butterfieldoverlandstage.com/organizations-and-links/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Butterfield Overland Mail Company</a><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> o</span>perated the trail from 1858-1861, and Northwest Arkansas was home to numerous important stops along the way, most notably <a href=\"https://encyclopediaofarkansas.net/entries/fitzgerald-station-and-farmstead-8157/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Fitzgerald Station</a>, which still stands in Springdale.</li></ul><p>Find an interactive map of historic stops along the trail <a href=\"https://www.fayettevillehistory.org/2007/01/butterfield_tra.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"butterfield-trail-pending-president-s-signature-for-recognition-as-national-historic-trail"}},
